Package: PediHaplotyper
Type: Package
Version: 1.0
Title: PediHaplotyper assigns haploblock alleles based on phased marker data in pedigrees
Date: 2015-10-30
Author: Roeland E. Voorrips [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Roeland E. Voorrips, Wageningen University & Research <roeland.voorrips@wur.nl>
Depends: R (>= 3.0.0)
LazyData: true
Description: Haploblocks are groups of tightly linked markers that inherit as a single unit. 
    They can be considered as multi-allelic markers. PediHaplotyper assigns haploblock alleles 
	so they can be used for e.g. QTL mapping. Citation: Voorrips RE, Bink MCAM, 
	Kruisselbrink JW, Koehorst - van Putten HJJ, van de Weg WE (2016) PediHaplotyper: 
	Software for consistent assignment of marker haplotypes in pedigrees. 
	Mol Breeding (2016) 36:119. DOI 10.1007/s11032-016-0539-y
License: GPL (>=2)
